[div class=p 
	[em 
		"AMOK!
	]em
	" is a homebrew Odyssey2 game, developed by John Dondzila and published in 1998 - the first O2 game to be released in 15 years after the console was initially discontinued. As with many later O2 homebrew games, it also had a limited cartridge release.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The gameplay has been likened to that of arcade classic 
	[em 
		"Berzerk
	]em
	". The player has to shoot their way through enemy robots in top-down maze-like rooms and make their way to the exit. The walls are also electrified hazards, and running into one is instant death.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Noxxa 
